=\"three colorful DRAM sticks with different patterns such as cherry blossom\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"three colorful DRAM sticks with different patterns such as cherry blossom\" data-chomp-id=\"63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"675\" data-alt=\"three colorful DRAM sticks with different patterns such as cherry blossom\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eCorsair Custom Lab’s DRAM sticks.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: CORSAIR\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005\" data-recommend-id=\"image://63fc4c78fef5365cff33598ca699c005\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1200\" data-height=\"675\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"three colorful DRAM sticks with different patterns such as cherry blossom\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eNvidia’s chief executive wasn’t the only one sporting a new look at CES — Corsair (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://qz.com/quote/CRSR\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://qz.com/quote/CRSR\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eCRSR\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e) is bringing their Custom Lab creativity to DRAM sticks. They’ve got eight designs, including delicate cherry blossom and futuristic sci-fi light patterns, available in black, white, or gray. These aren’t just DRAM modules with a pretty paint job — they’re still high-performance memory. Looks like your PC’s memory is ready for its fashion moment.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"837\" data-height=\"567\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a photo of a hand wearing a thick silver band on its left ring finger\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"a photo of a hand wearing a thick silver band on its left ring finger\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"a photo of a hand wearing a thick silver band on its left ring finger\" data-chomp-id=\"b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"567\" data-alt=\"a photo of a hand wearing a thick silver band on its left ring finger\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eUltrahuman’s Rare ring.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Ultrahuman\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b03872cd5b9f441d486e34a1d4a7ab75\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"837\" data-height=\"567\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a photo of a hand wearing a thick silver band on its left ring finger\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eUltrahuman unveiled a smart ring in 18-karat gold for $1,900 (or $2,200 if you prefer platinum). At a time when other wearables like Humane’s AI Pin are struggling to find their footing, Ultrahuman is betting that luxury shoppers want their health tracking to come with a designer price tag. Functionally, it’s identical to their $350 Ring Air — but hey, at least this one’s named after desert dunes and comes with a lifetime subscription.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7\" data-recommend-id=\"image://7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7\" data-format=\"webp\" data-width=\"1024\" data-height=\"577\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"an image of the gaming chair with illustrated red and blue flows of air, the chair is in a dark space with a yellow glow on one side of the wall and blue light on the other side\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"an image of the gaming chair with illustrated red and blue flows of air, the chair is in a dark space with a yellow glow on one side of the wall and blue light on the other side\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"an image of the gaming chair with illustrated red and blue flows of air, the chair is in a dark space with a yellow glow on one side of the wall and blue light on the other side\" data-chomp-id=\"7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7\" data-format=\"webp\" data-height=\"577\" data-alt=\"an image of the gaming chair with illustrated red and blue flows of air, the chair is in a dark space with a yellow glow on one side of the wall and blue light on the other side\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eRazer’s Project Arielle mesh gaming chair with an integrated fan system.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Razer\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7\" data-recommend-id=\"image://7b12b20781df25e9e46bfcf4c8190ab7\" data-format=\"webp\" data-width=\"1024\" data-height=\"577\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"an image of the gaming chair with illustrated red and blue flows of air, the chair is in a dark space with a yellow glow on one side of the wall and blue light on the other side\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eRazer has a new take on gaming comfort — their prototype gaming chair can blast you with hot or cold air. And because this is Razer at CES, of course, this temperature-controlled chair needed a dramatic name: Project Arielle. The chair uses a bladeless fan system that can cool you down during intense gaming sessions or warm you up on chilly days. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eUnlike most of Razer’s wild CES concepts (remember that \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.theverge.com/ces/2017/1/5/14112686/razer-project-valerie-multi-monitor-gaming-laptop-concept\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/ces/2017/1/5/14112686/razer-project-valerie-multi-monitor-gaming-laptop-concept\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003efold-out triple-screen laptop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e?), this one actually seems practical, if a little decadent. Though you’ll have to stay plugged in — spinning 360 degrees will turn you into a power cable mummy.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8\" data-recommend-id=\"image://116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"714\" data-height=\"398\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a screenshot of a player playing fortnite with his AI agent in the bottom right corner\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"a screenshot of a player playing fortnite with his AI agent in the bottom right corner\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 37.31em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 37.37em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"a screenshot of a player playing fortnite with his AI agent in the bottom right corner\" data-chomp-id=\"116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"398\" data-alt=\"a screenshot of a player playing fortnite with his AI agent in the bottom right corner\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eStreamlabs, Inworld AI, and Nvidia’s AI agent for streaming. \u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Streamlabs on YouTube\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8\" data-recommend-id=\"image://116d7ab5fcca8c1ee3d4e3511300f5f8\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"714\" data-height=\"398\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a screenshot of a player playing fortnite with his AI agent in the bottom right corner\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eNow AI wants to be your gaming buddy — or your worst critic. Inworld AI and Streamlabs (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://qz.com/quote/LOGI\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://qz.com/quote/LOGI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eLOGI\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e) are cooking up an ‘Intelligent Streaming Assistant’ that can hype up your Fortnite victories or, presumably, roast your building skills. It’ll even trigger special effects when you do something impressive, though based on the demo, it looks about as natural as a robot trying to do stand-up comedy. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWant a sassy AI cohost commenting on your gameplay? Coming to Streamlabs later this year, your mileage may vary depending on your gaming and how able you can handle some heckling.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe\" data-recommend-id=\"image://fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2200\" data-height=\"1438\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a smart garden lamp displayed in a dark room of a home\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"a smart garden lamp displayed in a dark room of a home\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"a smart garden lamp displayed in a dark room of a home\" data-chomp-id=\"fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1438\" data-alt=\"a smart garden lamp displayed in a dark room of a home\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eLG Electronics’ smart garden standing lamp.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: LG Electronics\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe\" data-recommend-id=\"image://fd434a92ae165b3e0581af3bcd550ebe\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2200\" data-height=\"1438\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"a smart garden lamp displayed in a dark room of a home\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eLG (\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://qz.com/quote/LPL\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://qz.com/quote/LPL\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eLPL\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e) is bringing together two things we never knew we needed combined: a smart lamp and an indoor garden. Their new floor-standing light doubles as a plant sanctuary, with LED lighting that can both nurture your greenery and set the mood. It’s got a clever shelf in the middle for growing up to twenty plants, and a built-in watering system that knows exactly what your leafy friends need.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e Finally, a smart home gadget that might actually make your home feel more alive — though, like many of LG’s coolest innovations revealed at CES, there’s no guarantee it’ll make it to stores near you any time soon.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896\" data-recommend-id=\"image://cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896\" data-format=\"webp\" data-width=\"1250\" data-height=\"833\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of the Hormometer displayed on a phone, a thermometer is beside the phone and two screenshots of the product display are in the image\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of the Hormometer displayed on a phone, a thermometer is beside the phone and two screenshots of the product display are in the image\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"image of the Hormometer displayed on a phone, a thermometer is beside the phone and two screenshots of the product display are in the image\" data-chomp-id=\"cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896\" data-format=\"webp\" data-height=\"833\" data-alt=\"image of the Hormometer displayed on a phone, a thermometer is beside the phone and two screenshots of the product display are in the image\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eHormometer\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Consumer Electronics Show (CES)\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896\" data-recommend-id=\"image://cf3bcef8d0569c59c21bba2bb5997896\" data-format=\"webp\" data-width=\"1250\" data-height=\"833\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of the Hormometer displayed on a phone, a thermometer is beside the phone and two screenshots of the product display are in the image\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eTired of just tracking your steps and sleep? The Hormometer wants you to check your hormones, too. It’s a simple stick that uses your saliva and phone camera to measure stress and reproductive hormones like cortisol and progesterone. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAt $8 a month, it’s way cheaper than traditional lab tests — though experts are raising eyebrows at the whole ‘hormone balancing’ trend it’s riding. Still, for anyone dealing with actual hormone-related health issues, having lab-quality results without the lab visit could be a game-changer.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59\" data-recommend-id=\"image://2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2700\" data-height=\"1800\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Dreame Technology\u0026#39;s ultra robot vacuum shown tilted up on its \u0026#34;legs\u0026#34;\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Dreame Technology\u0026#39;s ultra robot vacuum shown tilted up on its \u0026#34;legs\u0026#34;\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Dreame Technology\u0026#39;s ultra robot vacuum shown tilted up on its \u0026#34;legs\u0026#34;\" data-chomp-id=\"2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1800\" data-alt=\"Dreame Technology\u0026#39;s ultra robot vacuum shown tilted up on its \u0026#34;legs\u0026#34;\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e Dreame Technology’s X50 Ultra robot vacuum.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto: Dreame Technology\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59\" data-recommend-id=\"image://2f7cfc1a3eab33db3c49fedabb4aab59\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"2700\" data-height=\"1800\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Dreame Technology\u0026#39;s ultra robot vacuum shown tilted up on its \u0026#34;legs\u0026#34;\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eFirst they tracked our steps, now the robots are taking their own. Dreame’s new X50 Ultra vacuum can push itself up and onto spots that are up to 2.5 inches high with what they’re calling a “motorized swing arm” (but come on, those are definitely legs). While it’s not ready to climb a set of normal stairs, this is a big leap forward from the robot vacuums that struggle with thick rugs. Baby steps, right?\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5\" data-recommend-id=\"image://d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"903\" data-height=\"603\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of LG\u0026#39;s transparent TV displayed in a bedroom against a glass wall with a moon on the screen\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of LG\u0026#39;s transparent TV displayed in a bedroom against a glass wall with a moon on the screen\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"image of LG\u0026#39;s transparent TV displayed in a bedroom against a glass wall with a moon on the screen\" data-chomp-id=\"d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"603\" data-alt=\"image of LG\u0026#39;s transparent TV displayed in a bedroom against a glass wall with a moon on the screen\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eLG Signature OLED T transparent 4K Smart TV.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: LG Electronics\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5\" data-recommend-id=\"image://d985b8ff60388e8f3ec4566c1b771bf5\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"903\" data-height=\"603\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"image of LG\u0026#39;s transparent TV displayed in a bedroom against a glass wall with a moon on the screen\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eLG just revealed a television you can literally see through. Their new OLED T switches between regular TV and completely transparent at the press of a button — when it’s off, it looks like a window.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAt $60,000, it’s definitely not for everyone (the reviews are having a field day with that price tag). But even the skeptics have to admit there’s something magical about a TV that can transform into a virtual fish tank. However, as \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/8/24029590/lg-oled-t-transparent-tv-announced-specs-features\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/8/24029590/lg-oled-t-transparent-tv-announced-specs-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eThe Verge points out\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, maybe the real question is how long before you get tired of watching your shows through what’s essentially a very expensive window?”\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThis story originally appeared on Quartz, our sister site, on January 9.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
